	// S / L / H monogram as `progress` goes 0 → 1.
	//
	// Each glyph (one <path> each; READING_POS de-scrambles the SVG's path order)
	// owns a precomputed scroll threshold: it disappears once progress passes it.
	// Thresholds follow a tail-first trend, but a deterministic per-glyph jitter
	// (baked at generation time — stable across renders) shuffles neighbours and
	// unevens the gaps so the dissolve reads as organic, not metronomic. Monogram
	// glyphs (first of each line) never disappear.
	//
	// Pass progress={1} for the resting monogram (About, Index); the homepage
	// drives it from scroll. Hovering anywhere on the mark types the full name
	// back in: a tweened factor glides 1 → 0, sweeping the effective progress
	// down through the per-letter thresholds so glyphs reappear in their
